"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[2909],{2909:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"id":1,"title":"Mission n\xb01 : Create the School of the Future","description":"Introduction of the Nexus and Starter Packs, and establishment of a task force to create the school of the future.","content":{"html":"<h2 id=\\"336046aa-722c-45c2-9e8e-a5915b1c8b51\\">Introduction</h2>\\n<p>Today, the best courses and tutorials ever created are available for free and openly on the internet. The problem is that they are hard to find, and most people don\'t even know they exist. In other words, simply making the best content on the internet accessible to everyone would be enough to radically transform society into one that is fairer, more aware, and more productive. And this is nothing less than the first step toward creating \\"the school of the future.\\"</p>\\n<p>This article has two objectives:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>To present two basic solutions to quickly and easily start building the school of the future</li>\\n<li>To create a working group within the Metarevolution to coordinate initiatives aimed at creating the school of the future</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Let\'s start with the first point.</p>\\n<h2 id=\\"644c57ce-3e6f-43e8-aee6-e6c0eb65a0a3\\">Part 1: 2 Basic Solutions</h2>\\n<p>The two solutions I\'m going to present here address one of society\'s major current problems: the lack of centralization and synthesis of information. These two solutions aren\'t meant to be perfect, but rather to serve as <a href=\\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preuve_de_concept\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\">proofs of concept</a>. In practical terms, if a simple website hosted for free on GitHub can significantly improve the transmission of important information, imagine what we will be able to accomplish together with just a little more resources.</p>\\n<p>For now, these two solutions are in beta. I\'ll improve them over time, potentially with your help.</p>\\n<h3 id=\\"962ba0fe-51c4-4f74-b8c7-d84300391928\\">Solution 1: Nexus (indexing the best content on the internet to learn everything)</h3>\\n<p>The word \\"nexus\\" comes from the Latin <em>nexus</em>, meaning \\"linked\\", and refers to the meeting point of multiple connections. Thus, the \\"Nexus\\" of the Metarevolution is a kind of search engine that provides access to a selection of the best content centralized on <a href=\\"/nexus\\">a page</a>.</p>\\n<p>There you will find, for example (note that this content is in French):</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>The reference for the best current book on consciousness</li>\\n<li>A 10-hour introductory course on materials science from the best engineering school in Switzerland (where a professor jumps on plates to test their strength)</li>\\n<li>The world\'s leading course for understanding computer science starting with 0 and 1</li>\\n<li>3 hours of video to understand the history of architecture and how to organize the chaos</li>\\n<li>A 10-hour lecture series to understand the basics of genetics and the genetic history of Homo sapiens around the world</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>The goal is to enable anyone who wishes to do so to explore any topics that interest them in greater depth by providing easy access to excellent content. The aim is not to replace universities, but to allow everyone to develop a general scientific and historical knowledge base through a sort of \\"Netflix of knowledge.\\" In other words, to democratize access to science and history by going beyond simple popular science.</p>\\n<p>Now, the value of Nexus lies precisely in the quality of its content selection. I vouch for the quality of this selection. You can <a href=\\"https://github.com/Metarevolution-v0/Metarevolution-v0.github.io#english\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\">submit content here</a>.</p>\\n<p>The long-term goal is for Nexus to be multilingual or, at the very least, to have an English-language version. I am therefore looking for an English speaker to be in charge of the English section of Nexus. That is, to select the best content in English to explore all topics in depth.</p>\\n<p>Finally, the idea behind Nexus isn\'t revolutionary and has already been tried before, but I haven\'t found anything satisfactory. If you let me know that someone has already done the work—and done it better than I have—I\'ll link to their site. The only thing that matters to me is that such a tool exists.</p>\\n<h3 id=\\"2839542a-844a-477e-8915-b185814ecf74\\">Solution 2: Starter Pack (synthesize the essentials for living in the modern age)</h3>\\n<p>A \\"starter pack\\" refers to a set of items that allows you to start playing a video game under optimal conditions. The Metarevolution starter packs aim to provide all the tools and techniques you need to know to thrive in the modern world. For example, <a href=\\"/starterpack/1\\">the first starter pack</a> lists the best tools and practices for effectively using the internet, computers, and AI.</p>\\n<p>Starter packs address two observations:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>There are thousands of websites and videos that say more or less the same thing, yet none have provided a satisfactory synthesis</li>\\n<li>The school of the future must teach everything: from science to how to find an apartment and optimize your meals</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>More generally, in today\'s society, there is a huge problem with the transfer of knowledge, particularly between generations and regarding everyday topics. Each of us is left to fend for ourselves and must find solutions to our daily problems by searching the internet amid a vast and confusing sea of information. And this situation affects everyone. I recently spoke with a consultant who graduated a few years ago from HEC (France\'s top business school), and he was still taking notes in Google Docs, even though free software that\'s 100 times more efficient—like <a href=\\"https://obsidian.md/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\">Obsidian</a> (or at least <a href=\\"https://www.notion.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\">Notion</a>)—exists.</p>\\n<p>That said, this problem could be solved by compiling a list of essential tools and techniques in a single, centralized location. An additional challenge lies in disseminating this centralized page. The Metarevolution serves here as a vehicle for transporting and delivering relevant information to the widest possible audience.</p>\\n<h2 id=\\"3d6c94e2-3145-41d9-8890-0a148c09f29d\\">Part 2: A Working Group to Create the School of the Future</h2>\\n<p>The two previous solutions are merely a quick and easy way to get started, but the ultimate goal is indeed to create \\"the school of the future\\", whatever that may mean. Indeed, it is unclear what the school of the future will look like, but it is clear what it will not look like.</p>\\n<p>In the universities of the future, students won\'t have to share their course materials in secret because professors don\'t want them to, as is currently the case. And they won\'t be forced to attend class just to individually copy down a lecture (as in the Middle Ages) that their professor could have shared with them in full from day one (in just two clicks). And, most importantly, computer programming exams won\'t be taken on paper, as is currently the case at many universities.</p>\\n<p>That said, the idea of creating a working group to design \\"the school of the future\\" is based on three observations:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Many individuals want to bring about change in schools and propose new ideas, but they are not coordinating their efforts and do not even know one another</li>\\n<li>A significant number of these initiatives view the government as a monster that cannot be reformed, or even as an enemy</li>\\n<li>Most initiatives or efforts lack ambition</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>The purpose of the working group is therefore to:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Coordinate initiatives (which will prevent reinventing the wheel or becoming discouraged by isolation)</li>\\n<li>Demystify the government to facilitate dialogue (the government is not an abstract machine, but rather made up of human beings like you and me, and the only way to truly bring about change in schools in most countries is through government reforms)</li>\\n<li>Set ambitious goals: the objective is not to create yet another alternative school or to slightly improve students\' math skills, but to create the school of the future</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>More broadly, the goals are to:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Increase humanity\'s collective intelligence</li>\\n<li>Reduce injustices in access to information and education</li>\\n<li>Promote a culture of science</li>\\n<li>Boost worker productivity</li>\\n<li>Boost scientific research</li>\\n</ul>\\n<h2 id=\\"e2b61fe3-ff97-49f8-955b-519b2161ddd0\\">Conclusion: Contact Me</h2>\\n<p>In an ideal world, someone, somewhere, has decided to dedicate their life to creating the school of the future and shares the vision of the Metarevolution. This article brings us together, and all I have to do is refer members of the movement who want to participate in this mission to that person. If you are that person or intend to become one, please contact me.</p>\\n<p>More broadly, for now, I invite those working in education or on a related project to contact me: <a href=\\"mailto:contact.metarevolution@proton.me\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\">contact.metarevolution@proton.me</a></p>","toc":[{"id":"52ff57cd-0b34-4bc4-b8d6-3c612beb1833","text":"","level":1,"children":[{"id":"336046aa-722c-45c2-9e8e-a5915b1c8b51","text":"Introduction","level":2,"children":[]},{"id":"644c57ce-3e6f-43e8-aee6-e6c0eb65a0a3","text":"Part 1: 2 Basic Solutions","level":2,"children":[{"id":"962ba0fe-51c4-4f74-b8c7-d84300391928","text":"Solution 1: Nexus (indexing the best content on the internet to learn everything)","level":3,"children":[]},{"id":"2839542a-844a-477e-8915-b185814ecf74","text":"Solution 2: Starter Pack (synthesize the essentials for living in the modern age)","level":3,"children":[]}]},{"id":"3d6c94e2-3145-41d9-8890-0a148c09f29d","text":"Part 2: A Working Group to Create the School of the Future","level":2,"children":[]},{"id":"e2b61fe3-ff97-49f8-955b-519b2161ddd0","text":"Conclusion: Contact Me","level":2,"children":[]}]}],"footnotes":"","frontmatter":{}}}')}}]);